Phase 1.5 – Security Foundation

This is not Authentication. It provides the security infrastructure that authentication and every other module will rely on.

It should include:

Security Module
Helmet configuration
CORS configuration
CSP (Content Security Policy)
CSRF protection (where applicable)
Rate Limiting / Throttling
Security Headers
Request ID / Correlation ID
Encryption Service
Hashing Service
Secrets Management
Secure Cookie utilities
File upload security
Input sanitization
Output sanitization
XSS protection utilities
SQL injection protection helpers
Security middleware
Security interceptors
Security filters
Security logging
Security health monitoring

Do not implement login, JWT authentication, users, or permissions in this phase.

Phase 1.6 – API Foundation

This prepares every future API.

It should include:

API Module
API Versioning
Standard API Response Framework
API Error Framework
Global Request/Response Models
Swagger customization
API Documentation decorators
Pagination framework
Filtering framework
Sorting framework
Search framework
Bulk operation framework
API Metrics
API Logging
Request validation
Response transformation
API testing infrastructure


